Impedance is:

a) the dependence of electrical circuit resistance on the alternating current frequency b) the active (ohmic) circuit resistance;

c) the reactive (capacitive and inductive) circuit resistance;

d) the total electrical circuit resistance to alternative current.

Non Newtonian fluids are a) fluids whose viscosity depends on shear rate;

b) fluids whose viscosity does not depend on pressure;

c) fluids whose flow is always turbulent;

d) fluids whose viscosity does not depend on temperature.

When light passes through a substance with the thickness of 2.07 cm its intensity decreases 
to one-half of initial value. What is the absorption coefficient of the substance (in cm-1
)?
